What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I learned a lot about the big picture structure of the Air Force including the domains of warfare, joint structure, and foreign relations.

narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I thoroughly enjoyed the daily discourse and thought it was a great addition to a course that could sometimes be dry. I also thought the guest speakers provided a lot of insight into not only the topics of the course, but also being an officer in the Air Force.
It was enjoyable due to the amount of unique discussions on a variety of topics as well as the integration of guest speakers.

narratives.question_text: Among the practices in this course geared toward learning during the COVID-19 pandemic, which succeeded and which could be improved? Please comment on course practices that allowed for virtual engagement. (Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: The virtual aspect and discussions were as good as they possibly be given the cicrcumstances and the virtual platform allowed for more guest speakers which was a plus.
The synchronous seminars with high student interaction was key.

narratives.question_text:
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I would recommend the course to anyone who is required to take it for ROTC
